tzgGFe0UG2Dxq6DT8EWXhVqENkpxuSVeBW8D2HC9-DZQvkuSeFCG3f5q9yebLhrgOwusXH1ERNk=
_m6fovXmQTCH-pFXmih0HEOJ-OGWSI7Ma6ZoLdUP9vTvcLIfqDDqXDdHy_2BzSt63-GVXPaLCCX=
4_7_TJHB9Js37hpCb7i4UukKpaRA ) :

Obviously a lot of what we are doing in Mixed Reality has been informed wit=
h what we have done in HoloLens and what we are seeing in terms there, espe=
cially since we focused it very quickly after its initial launch on the ent=
erprise and the business use cases and we=E2=80=99ve learned a lot. But the=
 way I come at it, Ben, is that I like to separate out, =E2=80=9CWhat is th=
e system, what are the apps=E2=80=9D? Of course, we want to bring the two t=
hings together where we can create magic, but at the same time, I also want=
 our application experiences in particular to be available on all platforms=
, that=E2=80=99s very central to how our strategy is.

For example, when I think about the Metaverse, the first thing I think abou=
t is it=E2=80=99s not going to be born in isolation from everything else th=
at=E2=80=99s in our lives, which is you=E2=80=99re going to have a Mac or a=
 Windows PC, you=E2=80=99re going to have an iOS or an Android phone, and m=
aybe you=E2=80=99ll have a headset. So if that is your life, how do we brin=
g, especially Microsoft 365, all of the relationships that are set up, the =
work artifacts I=E2=80=99ve set up all to life in that ecosystem of devices=
? That=E2=80=99s at least how I come to it and that=E2=80=99s where when Ma=
rk started talking to us about his next generation stuff around Quest was p=
retty exciting so it made a lot of sense for us to bring =E2=80=94 whether =
it=E2=80=99s Teams with its immersive meetings experience to Quest or wheth=
er it=E2=80=99s even Windows 365 streaming, and then, of course, all our ma=
nagement and security and even Xbox, that=E2=80=99s what is the motivation =
behind it.

In short, Microsoft is, from the top-down, a services-not-devices ( https:/=
/stratechery.com/2013/services-not-devices/?access_token=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1=
NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJhdW=
QiOiJzdHJhdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9ydC5vbmxpbmUiLCJlbnQiOnsidXJpIjpbImh0dHBzOi8vc=
3RyYXRlY2hlcnkuY29tLzIwMTMvc2VydmljZXMtbm90LWRldmljZXMvIl19LCJleHAiOjE2Nzcx=
NTkxMTksImlhdCI6MTY3NDU2NzExOSwiaXNzIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9zdHJhdGVjaGVyeS5wYXNzcG9=
ydC5vbmxpbmUvb2F1dGgiLCJzY29wZSI6ImZlZWQ6cmVhZCBhcnRpY2xlOnJlYWQgYXNzZXQ6cm=
VhZCBjYXRlZ29yeTpyZWFkIiwic3ViIjoiUnNldVlFOGpnSGVQcFdKZjFmQWI0QyIsInVzZSI6I=
mFjY2VzcyJ9.g9RRwb33o_vwPAF-fYbfK3FhfS4mGbfcR8mVZDsW8zCkZlSYU2o5uqm2tyw9_6B=
Tax19hlVeDHRpOelanf2u0r08cr07xezP1nf-8Wh7uco4UEP6VMvRquz7o0rc9O4UwlbHjeTuPa=
IaqAVFYXegrfp_3YkteNmHnxZ8ZoOFpq5b4WLpM1XQI_EngFkR5Ua4j-SYwPdQytaRElnLBEnQH=
cnuFeHYKPBjZ8ZP_uk4NXlpbDz2r4_jSUudWXASbe_8zF0AJqFUNs7xbZaWl1x8l4AwCkAKMVxm=
XfnHc_QXXiZT9drDf5x1iu-iVO59q8jw59zImI6yCLJuNGVcFaphxg ) company; that mean=
s that building its own hardware is a distraction from its mission, which i=
s to be available on every device. To that end, HoloLens stopped making sen=
se a while ago, and that extends to MRTK; Microsoft=E2=80=99s goal is to be=
 the best productivity experience on Oculus, the best productivity experien=
ce on Apple=E2=80=99s headset, whenever it launches, and anything else in t=
he market. Microsoft isn=E2=80=99t abandoning the Metaverse, it=E2=80=99s j=
ust hedging its bets, and in a way that is very much aligned with the compa=
ny=E2=80=99s overall strategy.

In other words, these are layoffs that both make sense and that were, in ma=
ny respects, telegraphed for months given Microsoft=E2=80=99s shift away fr=
om HoloLens last summer and commitment to Meta last fall.

